de a compelling match for **3,5-bis(4-chlorophenyl)-1,2,4-thiadiazole**. The 1,2,3-thiadiazole carbons typically appear at lower fields (<160 ppm).\n6.  **Conclusion:** The data uniquely identifies the molecule as **3,5-bis(4-chlorophenyl)-1,2,4-thiadiazole**.\n\nFINAL_RESULT:\n  UUID: 31eb1a1a-5584-4ef7-bed0-200bdd586307\n  PREDICTED_SMILES: Clc1ccc(cc1)c2nc(sn2)c3ccc(Cl)cc3\n  CONFIDENCE: 0.98\n  REASON_BRIEF: The 1H NMR shows two distinct para-chlorophenyl environments, ruling out symmetric thiadiazole isomers (1,3,4 or 1,2,5). The 13C NMR shifts at 187.1 and 172.9 ppm perfectly match the C5 and C3 carbons of a 1,2,4-thiadiazole core.",
